HEADWORD: Menthene
<hw>Men"thene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Menth</ets>ol
+ terp<ets>ene</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A colorless liquid
hydrocarbon resembling oil of turpentine, obtained by dehydrating
menthol. It has an agreeable odor and a cooling taste.</def>⟦br⟧
